    "minides": "A proper old-school 4x4 with a Mercedes-derived diesel engine, mechanical front and rear differential locks, and genuine expedition-grade off-road hardware.",
    "description": "The Force Gurkha 3-Door is a hardcore, ladder-frame off-roader aimed squarely at serious off-road enthusiasts rather than urban SUV buyers. It is powered by a Mercedes-derived 2.6-litre FM2.6 diesel engine producing 140 PS and 320 Nm, paired exclusively with a 5-speed manual gearbox and a genuine 4x4 system offering electric shift-on-the-fly between 2H, 4H, and 4L, plus rare-for-the-segment manual front and rear differential locks. It offers 700mm water-wading depth (thanks to a factory snorkel), 233mm ground clearance, and steep 39-degree approach / 37-degree departure angles. Despite its rugged focus, it has gained modern touches like a 9-inch touchscreen with Android Auto and Apple CarPlay, a digital instrument cluster, LED Pro Edge headlamps, and 18-inch alloy wheels. It is sold in a single, fully-loaded 4-seater variant and has also been supplied in bulk to the Indian Defence Forces."
  },
